    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1891</hi>.</date>
                            (Received October 31.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan reports that the investigation of the assault upon the <hi rend="italic">Baltimore’s</hi> men is secret; that, as he is informed,
                        Capt. Schley and the United States consul have received from the judge of
                        crime an invitation to submit evidence and will refer the application to the
                        legation, and that he will await instructions.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
